Buffy

00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:30.180
Joss Whedon’s love of foreshadowing got
to be put to full use with Buffy the Vampire

00:05:30.180 --> 00:05:35.449
slayer, planting seeds for future twists both
big and small. Season 4 of the series earned

00:05:35.449 --> 00:05:44.719
praise for having Willow come out, and enter
into a relationship with her girlfriend Tara.

00:05:44.719 --> 00:05:48.419
But an entire season before, the twist was
predicted when a vampire version of Willow

00:05:48.419 --> 00:05:51.500
from an alternate universe made a pass at
her.

00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:55.669
But some clues were far more serious. In the
Season 3 finale, Buffy’s dream sequence

00:05:55.669 --> 00:06:04.150
included some cryptic references, courtesy
of her ally-turned-enemy Faith. The nursery

00:06:04.150 --> 00:06:08.999
rhyme reference referred to Buffy’s sister,
arriving in the next season. 7-3-0, on the

00:06:08.999 --> 00:06:13.850
other hand, means 730 days, or exactly two
years - the time that would pass between that

00:06:13.850 --> 00:06:18.340
episode and the Season 5 finale, in which
Buffy would sacrifice herself (for the first

00:06:18.340 --> 00:06:22.969
time). Even if fans had deciphered the message,
two years wouldn’t have been enough time

00:06:22.969 --> 00:06:25.300
to prepare themselves.

